### While Loop Pattern in Go

Go doesn't have a `while` keyword. Use `for` with only a condition.

### For as While

```go
// Equivalent to while(condition)
sum := 1
for sum < 1000 {
    sum += sum
}
```

### Do-While Pattern

Use `for` with a break condition at the end:

```go
// Do-while equivalent
for {
    // do work
    if condition {
        break
    }
}
```

### Sentinel-Controlled Loop

```go
scanner := bufio.NewScanner(os.Stdin)
for scanner.Scan() {
    line := scanner.Text()
    if line == "" {
        break
    }
    fmt.Println("Got:", line)
}
```

### Flag-Controlled Loop

```go
running := true
for running {
    // process
    if shouldStop {
        running = false
    }
}
```

### Common While Patterns

| Pattern | Go Code |
|---------|---------|
| while (cond) | `for cond { }` |
| do { } while (cond) | `for { }` with break |
| while (true) | `for { }` |
| while (--i) | `for ; i > 0; i-- { }` |

> **Key Point:** Any `while` loop from other languages can be written as `for` with just the condition. This keeps Go's syntax simple and uniform.

codeExample:
package main

import "fmt"

func main() {
    // While pattern
    n := 10
    for n > 0 {
        fmt.Println(n)
        n--
    }

    // Do-while pattern
    x := 0
    for {
        fmt.Println("x =", x)
        x++
        if x >= 3 {
            break
        }
    }
}
